msgctxt "an7.55:8.5"
msgid ""
"So pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā uddhaṃsoto hoti "
"akaniṭṭhagāmī."
msgstr ""
"With the ending of the five lower fetters they head upstream, going to the "
"Akaniṭṭha realm."

msgctxt "an7.55:8.6"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, divasaṃsantatte ayokapāle haññamāne papaṭikā "
"nibbattitvā uppatitvā mahante tiṇapuñje vā kaṭṭhapuñje vā nipateyya."
msgstr ""
"Suppose you struck an iron pot that had been heated all day. Any spark that "
"flew off and floated away would fall on a huge heap of grass or twigs."

#. VAR: daheyya → ḍaheyya (aññattha)
#. VAR: pathantaṃ vā → panthantaṃ vā (bj) | patthantaṃ vā (pts1)
msgctxt "an7.55:8.7"
msgid ""
"Sā tattha aggimpi janeyya, dhūmampi janeyya, aggimpi janetvā dhūmampi "
"janetvā tameva mahantaṃ tiṇapuñjaṃ vā kaṭṭhapuñjaṃ vā pariyādiyitvā "
"gacchampi daheyya, dāyampi daheyya, gacchampi dahitvā dāyampi dahitvā "
"haritantaṃ vā pathantaṃ vā selantaṃ vā udakantaṃ vā ramaṇīyaṃ vā bhūmibhāgaṃ "
"āgamma anāhārā nibbāyeyya."
msgstr ""
"There it would ignite a fire and produce smoke. And after consuming the "
"grass and twigs, the fire would burn up plants and trees until it reached a "
"green field, a roadside, a cliff’s edge, a body of water, or cleared "
"parkland, where it would be extinguished for lack of fuel."

msgctxt "an7.55:8.8"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃ paṭipanno hoti:"
msgstr "In the same way, a mendicant who practices like this …"

msgctxt "an7.55:8.9"
msgid "‘no cassa no ca me siyā … pe …"
msgstr "‘It might not be, and it might not be mine. …’"

msgctxt "an7.55:8.10"
msgid ""
"so pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā uddhaṃsoto hoti "
"akaniṭṭhagāmī."
msgstr ""
"With the ending of the five lower fetters they head upstream, going to the "
"Akaniṭṭha realm."

msgctxt "an7.55:8.11"
msgid "Imā kho, bhikkhave, satta purisagatiyo."
msgstr "These are the seven places people are reborn."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an7.55:9.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, anupādāparinibbānaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is extinguishment by not grasping?"

msgctxt "an7.55:9.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃ paṭipanno hoti:"
msgstr "Take a mendicant who practices like this:"

msgctxt "an7.55:9.3"
msgid ""
"‘no cassa no ca me siyā, na bhavissati na me bhavissati, yadatthi yaṃ bhūtaṃ "
"taṃ pajahāmī’ti upekkhaṃ paṭilabhati."
msgstr ""
"‘It might not be, and it might not be mine. It will not be, and it will not "
"be mine. I am giving up what exists, what has come to be.’ They gain "
"equanimity."

msgctxt "an7.55:9.4"
msgid ""
"So bhave na rajjati, sambhave na rajjati, atthuttari padaṃ santaṃ "
"sammappaññāya passati."
msgstr ""
"They’re not attached to life, or to creating a new life. And they see with "
"right wisdom that there is a peaceful state beyond."

msgctxt "an7.55:9.5"
msgid ""
"Tañca khvassa padaṃ sabbena sabbaṃ sacchikataṃ hoti, tassa sabbena sabbaṃ "
"mānānusayo pahīno hoti, sabbena sabbaṃ bhavarāgānusayo pahīno hoti, sabbena "
"sabbaṃ avijjānusayo pahīno hoti."
msgstr ""
"And they have totally realized that state. They’ve completely given up the "
"underlying tendencies of conceit, attachment to life, and ignorance."

msgctxt "an7.55:9.6"
msgid "So āsavānaṃ khayā … pe … sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"They’ve realized the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in "
"this very life, and live having realized it with their own insight due to "
"the ending of defilements."

msgctxt "an7.55:9.7"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, anupādāparinibbānaṃ."
msgstr "This is called extinguishment by not grasping."

msgctxt "an7.55:9.8"
msgid "Imā kho, bhikkhave, satta purisagatiyo anupādā ca parinibbānan”ti."
msgstr ""
"These are the seven places people are reborn, and extinguishment by not "
"grasping.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an7.55:9.9"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
